---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Words Containing QU — Essential Scrabble Q Words"
  description="Master QU words in Scrabble from 3-8 letters. Free ranked list with scores, definitions, and strategies for playing the Q tile effectively every game."
  keywords="scrabble words with qu, qu words scrabble, q words list, best qu words, scrabble q strategy, words containing qu scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Words Containing QU — Essential Scrabble Q Words",
    "description": "Master QU words in Scrabble from 3-8 letters. Free ranked list with scores, definitions, and strategies for playing the Q tile effectively every game.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-14",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/words-containing-qu" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What are the highest-scoring QU words in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "SQUEEZE scores 25 points, QUINZE scores 24, QUARTZ scores 24, and QUARTZITE scores 27. For shorter words, QUIZ (22 pts), QUAFF (20 pts), and QUICK (20 pts) deliver excellent per-tile efficiency. The Q tile is worth 10 points, making every QU word inherently high-scoring." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How many QU words should a Scrabble player memorize?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Memorize at least 20-30 QU words across different lengths. Focus on short ones first (3-5 letters) since they fit more board positions: QUA, QUAD, QUAY, QUAFF, QUEEN, QUERY, QUICK, QUIET, QUILT, QUIRK, QUOTA, and QUOTE. Then learn 6-7 letter words for bingo potential." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What should you do if you have Q but no U in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Play Q-without-U words: QI (11 pts), QOPH (18 pts), QADI (14 pts), QANAT (14 pts), QAT (12 pts), QAID (14 pts), and QWERTY (21 pts). There are about 30 valid Q-without-U words in SOWPODS. If none fit the board, exchange the Q — holding it for multiple turns costs more points than trading." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Words Containing QU — Essential Scrabble Q Words</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-14">June 14, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>8 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        The Q tile strikes fear into many Scrabble players — 10 points of potential trapped on your rack if you can't find a play. But Q paired with U is one of the most reliable scoring combinations in the game. From the compact QUIZ (22 pts) to the devastating QUARTZ (24 pts), QU words deliver consistent high scores. Master this list and the Q becomes your friend, not your enemy.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top QU Words by Score</h2>

      <p>These are the most valuable QU words across all lengths. The Q's 10-point base value means even short QU words score well above average.</p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">#</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Word</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Points</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Definition</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">1</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">SQUEEZE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">25</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">To press tightly</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">2</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">QUARTZ</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">24</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A hard mineral</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">QUINZE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">24</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A card game (15)</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">QUIRKY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">22</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Peculiar or unusual</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">QUIZ</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">22</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A test of knowledge</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">QUAFF</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">20</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">To drink heartily</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">QUICK</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">20</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Fast or rapid</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">QUENCH</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">20</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">To satisfy a thirst</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">9</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">QUARRY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">18</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">An open excavation</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">QUORUM</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">17</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Minimum attendees needed</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">QUAY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">16</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A wharf for loading</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">QUILT</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">14</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A padded blanket</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">13</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">QUEEN</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">14</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A female monarch</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">14</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">QUOTA</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">14</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">An allotted amount</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">15</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">QUIET</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">14</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Making little noise</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">10 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Q tile value</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">1 tile</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Only Q in the bag</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">72 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">QUARTZ on TWS</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Short QU Words (3-4 Letters) — The Emergency Plays</h2>

      <p>When the board is tight and you need to play the Q quickly, these compact words fit almost anywhere.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">QUA</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">12 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">QUAD</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">14 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">QUAY</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">16 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">QUAG</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">14 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">QUIZ</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">22 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">QUIP</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">15 pts</span>
        </span>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 The Q Timing Rule</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Play the Q within <span class="text-white font-medium">2 turns of drawing it</span>. Every turn you hold the Q without playing costs you roughly 8-10 points in missed flexibility. The Q is worth 10 points but it blocks better plays while sitting on your rack. Quick deployment is key.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">QU Words for Bingo Potential (7+ Letters)</h2>

      <p>When you have the Q plus a strong rack, these longer QU words can earn the 50-point bingo bonus on top of already high base scores.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ 7-Letter QU Bingos</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">QUAKING (21+50), QUARREL (16+50), QUALIFY (22+50), QUARTER (16+50), QUEUING (17+50). These score 66-72+ points as bingos.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ 8-Letter QU Bingos</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">SQUANDER (18+50), QUESTING (18+50), ADEQUATE (18+50), QUOTIENT (17+50). Harder to play but devastating when they land.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">What If You Have Q but No U?</h2>

      <p>Don't panic. Several valid words use Q without U. These are your backup plan when the U tiles are already on the board or in your opponent's rack.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Q Without U</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">QI — 11 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">The most important 2-letter word in Scrabble. Valid in both TWL and SOWPODS.</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">QI (life force in Chinese philosophy) lets you play Q anywhere there's an I on the board. On a TLS, QI scores 31 points. Combined with a parallel play, it can exceed 40 points from just 2 tiles.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">QI</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">11 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">QOPH</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">18 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">QADI</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">14 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">QAT</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">12 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">QANAT</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">14 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">QWERTY</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">21 pts</span>
        </span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips for Playing QU Words</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Target premium squares with Q:</span> Q on a DLS = 20 points for one letter. Q on a TLS = 30 points. Always position Q words to maximize the Q tile's multiplier potential — even a modest word becomes excellent with Q on a premium square.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Hold U when you see Q coming:</span> Track tile draws. If the Q hasn't appeared and you have a U, keep it. The cost of holding one U is minimal compared to being stuck with Q and no U later.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Know QUEUE for vowel dumps:</span> QUEUE uses Q + 4 vowels (U, E, U, E). If you have Q + excess vowels, QUEUE solves both problems at once — plays the Q and dumps vowels simultaneously.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Don't hold Q past endgame:</span> An unplayed Q at game end costs you 10 points (subtracted from your score and added to opponent's). If you can't play Q within 2 turns of the endgame, exchange it immediately — even losing a turn is better than -10.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Summary</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">🎯 Summary</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">QU words are your <span class="text-white font-medium">high-value scoring engine</span>. QUIZ (22 pts), QUARTZ (24 pts), and QUAFF (20 pts) deliver massive points in compact packages. For emergencies, QI (11 pts) plays the Q without U. Memorize 20-30 QU words across all lengths, deploy Q within 2 turns of drawing it, and target premium squares for maximum multiplier impact.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/best-q-words-scrabble" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best Q Words in Scrabble — Top Scoring Q Plays</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/best-z-words-scrabble" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best Z Words in Scrabble — Top Scoring Z Plays</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/highest-scoring-scrabble-words" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Highest Scoring Scrabble Words Ever — Ultimate List</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-blue-800/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every QU word from your tiles — instant results, no signup</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-400 text-gray-950 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
